# Tailwind config — responsive additions

Tailwind 4 reads most theme tokens from `globals.css` (the `@theme` block). A
handful of things still belong in `tailwind.config.ts` — breakpoint names
(if they need explicit aliases beyond Tailwind defaults), content paths, and
plugin registration.

The defaults Tailwind ships are kept. The locked contract aligns to them, so no
breakpoint customization is needed in most projects.

## Default breakpoints (locked contract — DO NOT change without escalation)

| Name | Min-width | Pixel | Tier |
|---|---|---|---|
| `sm` | 40rem | 640px | Phone landscape, small tablet |
| `md` | 48rem | 768px | Tablet portrait |
| `lg` | 64rem | 1024px | Laptop, tablet landscape |
| `xl` | 80rem | 1280px | Desktop |
| `2xl` | 96rem | 1536px | Wide desktop |

If your project genuinely needs different breakpoints (e.g. an internal admin
that only targets 1280+, so `sm` becomes pointless), override in your CSS:

```css
@theme {
  --breakpoint-sm: 768px;
  --breakpoint-md: 1024px;
  --breakpoint-lg: 1280px;
  --breakpoint-xl: 1536px;
  --breakpoint-2xl: 1920px;
}
```

Don't introduce new breakpoint names. The five locked ones are what every
component is written against.

## Touch-target utilities

Already exposed via `--size-touch` and `--size-touch-lg` in `globals.css`. Use:

```html
<button class="min-h-touch min-w-touch">...</button>     <!-- 44×44 minimum -->
<button class="min-h-touch-lg min-w-touch-lg">...</button> <!-- 48×48 preferred -->
<button class="size-touch">...</button>                    <!-- exact 44×44 -->
```

## Fluid type and spacing utilities

Already exposed via `--text-fluid-*` and `--space-fluid-*` in `globals.css`.

Tailwind 4 auto-generates utilities from theme tokens, so these "just work":

- `text-fluid-base`, `text-fluid-lg`, `text-fluid-3xl`, etc.
- `gap-fluid-md`, `py-fluid-lg`, `mt-fluid-sm`, etc.
  (Tailwind reads `--space-fluid-*` as part of its spacing scale via the
  `@theme` directive — see Tailwind 4 docs on theme variable namespaces.)

If your Tailwind setup doesn't expand `--space-fluid-*` automatically into the
spacing scale (some setups require namespace prefixes), use the CSS-variable
form inline:

```html
<section class="py-[var(--space-fluid-lg)]">
```

## Container queries

Native in Tailwind 4. Use as:

```html
<div class="@container">
  <h2 class="text-fluid-xl @md:text-fluid-2xl">Adapts to parent</h2>
</div>
```

The `@sm:`, `@md:`, `@lg:`, `@xl:`, `@2xl:` prefixes work inside any
`@container` ancestor. Default container-query breakpoint values map to:

| Name | Min container width |
|---|---|
| `@sm` | 24rem (384px) |
| `@md` | 28rem (448px) |
| `@lg` | 32rem (512px) |
| `@xl` | 36rem (576px) |
| `@2xl` | 42rem (672px) |

NOTE: these are NOT the same as the viewport breakpoints — they're smaller,
because containers are typically narrower than viewports. This is intentional:
"`@md`" means "the container is at least 448px wide" — at that width a 2-column
layout is reasonable.

If you need to query at the viewport breakpoint values within a container, name
them explicitly:

```html
<div class="@container/card">
  <h2 class="@[768px]/card:text-fluid-2xl">...</h2>
</div>
```

The `/name` syntax names the container so children can target it. Rare; use
when component nesting requires disambiguation.
